			<h2 id="comments">Comment (1)
			</h2>
			<ol class="comments">
		
				<li id="comment-3133">
					<article>
						<p>I think blind people are going to require help when they buy drugs.  What happens if you&#8217;re trying to buy the above product and instead you buy laxatives?</p>
<p>I think a more useful tool would be scanning allowing blind people to scan RFID tags attached to each product and then using text-to-speech technology for identification.</p>
<p>This would be a fairly expensive system to implement, but there is already motivation for the stores to use RFID tags.  Custom boxes would probably be seen as an unnecessary expense.</p>
